# LexMastery Official Technology Stack

This file defines the ONLY approved technology stack for the project.

Cursor MUST follow these technologies.

Do not substitute alternatives unless explicitly instructed.

---

# Flutter

ALWAYS use the latest stable Flutter version.

ALWAYS use the latest stable Dart version.

Never generate deprecated Flutter code.

Always follow Material 3.

Use adaptive widgets where appropriate.

---

# Architecture

ALWAYS use Feature-First Clean Architecture.

Every feature MUST contain

presentation/

domain/

data/

Never mix responsibilities.

Never put business logic inside Widgets.

---

# State Management

ONLY use Riverpod.

Use:

flutter_riverpod

riverpod_annotation

riverpod_generator

Never use:

Provider

Bloc

Cubit

Redux

MobX

GetX

unless explicitly requested.

---

# Navigation

ALWAYS use go_router.

Support:

Deep Links

Nested Navigation

Shell Routes

Authentication Guards

Never use Navigator.push() directly except inside Router configuration.

---

# Networking

ONLY use Dio.

Every request must pass through

API Client

↓

Repository

↓

Use Case

↓

Controller

↓

UI

Never call Dio directly from Widgets.

---

# Serialization

Use

Freezed

json_serializable

Never manually write JSON parsing.

Always generate immutable models.

---

# Local Storage

Use Hive for offline caching.

Use flutter_secure_storage for

JWT

Refresh Tokens

Sensitive user information

Never store sensitive information inside Hive.

---

# Dependency Injection

Use Riverpod providers.

Avoid service locators.

Never use GetIt unless approved.

---

# Logging

Use logger.

Disable verbose logs in production.

Never print() in production code.

---

# Error Handling

Create typed Failure objects.

Never throw generic Exceptions.

Every network error must map to a user-friendly message.

---

# Images

Use cached_network_image.

Never use Image.network directly.

---

# Forms

Use flutter_form_builder when complexity requires it.

Otherwise use Flutter forms.

Validation belongs in the Controller.

---

# Animations

Use flutter_animate.

Avoid custom AnimationControllers unless necessary.

Prefer implicit animations.

---

# SVG

Use flutter_svg.

Never convert SVG to PNG.

---

# Responsive Layout

Use flutter_screenutil only for typography scaling if needed.

Do not scale everything.

Respect platform conventions.

---

# Localization

Prepare every string for localization.

Never hardcode UI strings inside Widgets.

---

# Theming

Use Theme Extensions.

Never hardcode colors.

Never hardcode font sizes.

Never hardcode spacing.

Everything must come from Design Tokens.

---

# Testing

Every feature should support

Unit Tests

Widget Tests

Integration Tests

Controllers should be fully testable.

---

# Performance

Prefer const constructors.

Minimize Widget rebuilds.

Use ConsumerWidget selectively.

Use select() where appropriate.

Lazy-load large modules.

Paginate large datasets.

---

# Analytics

Support Firebase Analytics.

Every major user interaction should be trackable.

---

# Crash Reporting

Use Firebase Crashlytics.

Never swallow exceptions silently.

---

# Notifications

Support Firebase Cloud Messaging.

Architecture should support

Push Notifications

Local Notifications

Scheduled Notifications

---

# Security

Never expose API Keys.

Never hardcode secrets.

Always use HTTPS.

Always validate tokens.

---

# Folder Naming

Use

snake_case

for folders.

PascalCase

for classes.

camelCase

for methods and variables.

---

# File Naming

home_screen.dart

login_controller.dart

course_repository.dart

progress_model.dart

Never abbreviate names.

---

# Package Rules

Before adding a package

Ask:

Can Flutter already do this?

Can an existing package already solve this?

Will this increase maintenance?

Keep dependencies minimal.

---

# Cursor Instructions

Always generate production-quality Flutter code.

Never generate demo code.

Never generate placeholder architecture.

Always follow this technology stack.

If a package conflicts with this file,

this file wins.